YAN KWOK
 
BEd in Music (Hon), HKIED
ATCL Recital Flute, Trinity
ATCL Recital Piano,Trinity
ABRSM Grade 8 Percussion 
 
Winner of 2nd HK Students Open Music Competition Diploma class, she received her Bachelor of Music Education at the Hong Kong Institute of Education in 2014, studying flute with Hong Kong Philharmonic Orchestra Freelance player Ivy Chuang and Matthew Wu, and attending Master classes and private lessons by professional flutist Shimizu Kazutaka, Markus Brönnimann, Roman Novotny. Apart from getting professional training in Hong Kong, Yan also got selected as Music exchange Student in Alverno College in the United State, studying with world known flutist Immanuel Davis, Jennifer Clippert and Linda Nielsen. Except studying flute, Yan also got professional training on piano, studying with Sze Yau Chan and Dr. Grace Yu from Hong Kong Academy for Performing Arts.
 
As a musician, she has engaged as a performer in Joyeux Winds, HKIED Symphonic Winds, HKIED Orchestra and Hong Kong International Band Fair as flutist, and HKIED Orchestra as percussionist. In addition to music background, she has over 5 years of private teaching experience in both piano, flute and percussion in music center, primary school, secondary school and church.
 
